  "prompt": "Which is the best DSLR under 2500?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, there are several excellent DSLR cameras available under $2500. The choice can depend on your specific needs, such as whether you're focused on photography, videography, or a mix of both. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Canon EOS 90D**:\n   - Sensor: 32.5 MP APS-C\n   - Video: 4K video recording\n   - Autofocus: Dual Pixel AF\n   - Versatile for both photography and videography.\n\n2. **Nikon D7500**:\n   - Sensor: 20.9 MP APS-C\n   - Video: 4K UHD video recording\n   - Great low-light performance and fast burst shooting.\n   - Good for both enthusiasts and advanced photographers.\n\n3. **Canon EOS Rebel T8i (EOS 850D)**:\n   - Sensor: 24.1 MP APS-C\n   - Video: 4K video recording\n   - User-friendly interface, ideal for beginners.\n   - Versatile for various photography styles.\n\n4. **Nikon D5600**:\n   - Sensor: 24.2 MP APS-C\n   - Video: Full HD 1080p video recording\n   - Great for photography, particularly for beginners and intermediate users.\n\n5. **Pentax K-70**:\n   - Sensor: 24 MP APS-C\n   - Weather-sealed body, good for outdoor shooting.\n   - Offers features like pixel shift resolution for enhanced image quality.\n\nAll of these options come with excellent image quality, robust features, and user-friendly controls. Make sure to consider what additional lenses or accessories you might need, which can influence your total cost. If you can, visit a camera shop to get a feel for each model before making a decision.",
